**Deprecated for active work.** Use `19-godot-agent-workflow.mdc` and [docs/DOC_INDEX.md](docs/DOC_INDEX.md).

Before coding (_archive/unity/ only):

- Read relevant docs in /docs.
- Identify the smallest useful change.
- Ask only if a decision blocks implementation.

When coding (Unity archive only — `_archive/unity/`):

- Keep changes focused.
- Prefer adding new files over large rewrites when safe.
- Preserve public APIs unless the task requires changing them.
- Update docs when architecture or data contracts change.
- Use TODO comments sparingly and only for real follow-up work.

After coding:

- Summarize changed files.
- Explain how to test in Unity.
- Mention known limitations.
- Suggest the next best development step.

Do not invent unavailable assets. Use placeholder sprites/prefabs when needed and mark them clearly.
